description: This dashboard provides  performance metrics for tomcat

targets.query: SELECT last(value) FROM "load_midterm" WHERE "host" =~ /^$host$/ AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time(10s) fill(null)
SELECT mean("init") FROM "memorypool" WHERE "attributeName" = 'Usage' AND "typeName" = 'type=MemoryPool,name=CMS Old Gen' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("init") FROM "memorypool" WHERE "attributeName" = 'Usage' AND "typeName" = 'type=MemoryPool,name=CMS Old Gen' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("init") FROM "memorypool" WHERE "attributeName" = 'Usage' AND "typeName" = 'type=MemoryPool,name=Code Cache' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("init") FROM "memorypool" WHERE "attributeName" = 'Usage' AND "typeName" = 'type=MemoryPool,name=Metaspace' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("init") FROM "memorypool" WHERE "attributeName" = 'Usage' AND "typeName" = 'type=MemoryPool,name=Metaspace' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("init") FROM "memorypool" WHERE "attributeName" = 'Usage' AND "typeName" = 'type=MemoryPool,name=Par Eden Space' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
SELECT mean("OpenFileDescriptorCount") FROM "OperatingSystem" WHERE "attributeName" = 'OpenFileDescriptorCount' AND $timeFilter GROUP BY time($interval) fill(null)
